obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (34545)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title `Prohibition of transfer of Post Office 5-year Cash Certificates without the consent of an authorised officer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 32 of 1920, s. 2, for certain words with effect from 1 -7-1965.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_95_00002_191718_1523342769327&sectionId=34545&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_95_00002_191718_1523342769327
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding any provision in any enactment or any rule of`
  line `law for the time being in force to the contrary, no transfer (whether made before or after the`
  line `commencement of this Act) of a Post Office 5-year Cash Certificate shall be valid without the`
  line `previous consent in writing of ^1[an officer of the Post Office authorised by general or special`
  line `order of the Central Government in that behalf].`
  line
  line `(2) In this section "transfer" means a transfer infer vivos and does not include a transfer by operation`
  line `of law.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (34546)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Payment on death of holder of Post Office 5-year Cash Certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_37_95_00002_191718_1523342769327&sectionId=34546&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_37_95_00002_191718_1523342769327
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) If a person dies`
  line `and is at the time of his death the holder of a Post Office 5-year Cash Certificate, payment of the`
  line `sum for the time being due on such certificate may be made in the manner provided in the`
  line `Government Savings Banks Act, 1873 (5 of 1873), for the payment of deposits belonging to the`
  line `estates of deceased persons, and the provisions of sections 4 to 9 of the said Act shall apply`
  line `accordingly as if the holder of such certificate were a depositor in a Government Savings Bank`
  line `and the sum for the time being due on such certificate were a deposit in such a Bank ^1[and as if`
  line `for the words "three thousand" in ^2[section 8] of the said Act the words "five thousand" were`
  line `substituted]:`
  line
  line `Provided that the powers conferred by the said provisions on the Secretary of a Government`
  line `Savings Bank shall be exercisable by the Post Master General for the area within which the post`
  line `office of issue of such certificate is situate ^3[or if that area is in Pakistan, by the Post Master`
  line `General for such area in India as the Central Government may by general or special order specify`
  line `in this behalf]:`
  line
  line `Provided further that, where in any one case payment is to be made of certificates issued`
  line `from more post offices than one, the said powers shall be exercisable by the Post Master General`
  line `for the area in which any of the said post offices is situate.`
  line
  line `(2) Nothing in sub-section (1) shall be deemed to require any person to accept payment of`
  line `the amount due on a Post Office 5-year Cash Certificate before the same has reached maturity.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 3, ibid.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 2 of 1943, s. 3, for "sections 4 and 8".`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by the A.O. 1948.`
